This is the name of a Federation space station.

The text of {SkyBox 99:src} reads:
▶ {loS... qIb HeHDaq, 'u' SepmeyDaq Sovbe'lu'bogh lenglu'meH He ghoSlu'bogh retlhDaq 'oHtaH. HaDlu'meH, QuSlu'meH, SuDlu'meH lojmIt Da logh Hop Hut tengchaH. vaj loghDaq lenglaHtaH Humanpu'. veH Qav 'oH logh'e'.:sen:nolink}

{chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n} = {lu-:v:pref,nolink}

When used with {-lu':v}, this prefix means "Someone (indefinite subject) does something to them".

This prefix is sometimes dropped for unknown reasons. While an error, this is often overlooked when clarity is not an issue, except in formal situations.[2]

▶ {tlhIngan qorDu' potlh:sen:nolink}
   {qorDu' lurDechmeyna' pab tlhInganpu'. qorDu' SaHlu'chugh 'ej matlhlu'chugh vaj wa' tlhIngan ghob potlhqu'. tlhIngan qorDu' pong potlh law' Hoch potlh puS.:sen:nolink}
  "Klingon Family Values
   With strong family traditions, devotion and loyalty to family is one of the most important Klingon virtues. Above all, the Klingon family name is highly valued."[2]
